# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorQueen1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "In the weeks that followed, Sarah allowed Carolyn to set the plans into motion."
    new "In the weeks that followed, Sarah allowed Carolyn to set the plans into motion."

    old "Using Carolyn's connections among the refugees, but common and noble alike, she gathered nearly a hundred people."
    new "Using Carolyn's connections among the refugees, but common and noble alike, she gathered nearly a hundred people."

    old "A hundred people, that together, represented the leadership of the refugees of Rosanna that had landed in Rahayal."
    new "A hundred people, that together, represented the leadership of the refugees of Rosanna that had landed in Rahayal."

    old "Under them, tens of thousands more. All equally loyal."
    new "Under them, tens of thousands more. All equally loyal."

    old "Before one another and under oath of the Gods, each swore their loyalty, vowing to uphold their oaths to house Rose."
    new "Before one another and under oath of the Gods, each swore their loyalty, vowing to uphold their oaths to house Rose."

    old "To Sarah."
    new "To Sarah."

    old "Her return had come to them as a surprise, but the people of Rosanna took it as an almost divine omen."
    new "Her return had come to them as a surprise, but the people of Rosanna took it as an almost divine omen."

    old "The heir, back from the dead, and with a warrior's gait."
    new "The heir, back from the dead, and with a warrior's gait."

    old "Their hearts swelled, and by now, many were eager for the carnage of war."
    new "Their hearts swelled, and by now, many were eager for the carnage of war."

    old "Gilead's Legions, as promised, arrived in the docks to mingle among her people."
    new "Gilead's Legions, as promised, arrived in the docks to mingle among her people."

    old "Prepared, hardened, they were the disciplined core of her army that she would have otherwise lacked."
    new "Prepared, hardened, they were the disciplined core of her army that she would have otherwise lacked."

    old "Gilead, meanwhile, had send no message."
    new "Gilead, meanwhile, had send no message."

    old "Her rejection had cooled whatever relationship Carolyn had tried to cultivate between them."
    new "Her rejection had cooled whatever relationship Carolyn had tried to cultivate between them."

    old "Sarah heard a soft sound behind her."
    new "Sarah heard a soft sound behind her."

    old "Turning away from the war map, she saw Samayra standing in the entrance to her room."
    new "Turning away from the war map, she saw Samayra standing in the entrance to her room."

    old "Sarah said her name softly."
    new "Sarah said her name softly."

    old "She had found herself ever more protective of the girl ever since deciding on her course."
    new "She had found herself ever more protective of the girl ever since deciding on her course."

    old "Samayra was proving herself useful as her secretary, a hundred times over, but they were heading into war."
    new "Samayra was proving herself useful as her secretary, a hundred times over, but they were heading into war."

    old "And the girl was not a warrior in heart or body."
    new "And the girl was not a warrior in heart or body."

    old "Commander."
    new "Commander."

    old "Samayra saluted."
    new "Samayra saluted."

    old "Sarah had told her many times over she didn't need to be so formal, but whenever she was officially on duty, she couldn't help herself."
    new "Sarah had told her many times over she didn't need to be so formal, but whenever she was officially on duty, she couldn't help herself."

    old "In the end, Sarah simply relented."
    new "In the end, Sarah simply relented."

    old "I came to deliver the final report."
    new "I came to deliver the final report."

    old "Sarah motioned at Samayra."
    new "Sarah motioned at Samayra."

    old "Final army count, complete. Quartermasters report full inventory. Last of the shipping contracts...signed."
    new "Final army count, complete. Quartermasters report full inventory. Last of the shipping contracts...signed."

    old "That was it, Sarah thought."
    new "That was it, Sarah thought."

    old "The report she had been equally waiting for and dreading."
    new "The report she had been equally waiting for and dreading."

    old "And...what about the equipment inspection?"
    new "And...what about the equipment inspection?"

    old "Completed as well, Commander."
    new "Completed as well, Commander."

    old "Perhaps, she thought, there might have been a way to delay it. Hold back a moment longer. Buy one more day of peace."
    new "Perhaps, she thought, there might have been a way to delay it. Hold back a moment longer. Buy one more day of peace."

    old "But nothing could be held back forever."
    new "But nothing could be held back forever."

    old "Commander..."
    new "Commander..."

    old "The men...they're standing in formation. In the harbor."
    new "The men...they're standing in formation. In the harbor."

    old "Samayra gestured towards the window."
    new "Samayra gestured towards the window."

    old "They're waiting for you to give them the sign."
    new "They're waiting for you to give them the sign."

    old "Looking at the window, Sarah saw a soft breeze play with the curtains."
    new "Looking at the window, Sarah saw a soft breeze play with the curtains."

    old "A last moment of peace, she thought to herself."
    new "A last moment of peace, she thought to herself."

    old "Thank you, Samayra..."
    new "Thank you, Samayra..."

    old "You can leave the report here, prepare yourself to board the flagship with the rest of the commanding staff."
    new "You can leave the report here, prepare yourself to board the flagship with the rest of the commanding staff."

    old "Samayra nodded, turned, and left."
    new "Samayra nodded, turned, and left."

    old "Sarah began to walk towards the window that led to the balcony."
    new "Sarah began to walk towards the window that led to the balcony."

    old "Open, she felt the breeze from just outside, the sun, blocked only partially by the curtains."
    new "Open, she felt the breeze from just outside, the sun, blocked only partially by the curtains."

    old "And, drifting atop the wind...voices..."
    new "And, drifting atop the wind...voices..."

    old "Thousands of them. Tens-of-thousands."
    new "Thousands of them. Tens-of-thousands."

    old "Eager and nervous, all at the same time."
    new "Eager and nervous, all at the same time."

    old "Sarah closed her eyes and prayed that she was doing the right thing."
    new "Sarah closed her eyes and prayed that she was doing the right thing."

    old "Are you proud of me..Father?"
    new "Are you proud of me..Father?"

    old "Opening her eyes, Sarah murdered her own hesitant heart and strode out onto the balcony."
    new "Opening her eyes, Sarah murdered her own hesitant heart and strode out onto the balcony."

    old "Sarah heard a loud sound behind her."
    new "Sarah heard a loud sound behind her."

    old "Turning away from the war map, she saw Kate standing in the entrance to her room."
    new "Turning away from the war map, she saw Kate standing in the entrance to her room."

    old "Kate saluted."
    new "Kate saluted."

    old "Sarah had told her many times over she didn't need to be so formal, but in these last few days she couldn't help herself."
    new "Sarah had told her many times over she didn't need to be so formal, but in these last few days she couldn't help herself."

    old "Sarah motioned at Kate."
    new "Sarah motioned at Kate."

    old "Kate gestured towards the window."
    new "Kate gestured towards the window."

    old "Thank you, Kate..."
    new "Thank you, Kate..."

    old "Kate nodded, turned, and left."
    new "Kate nodded, turned, and left."

    old "As she passed through the curtains and the first people in the crowd began to see her, their voices grew."
    new "As she passed through the curtains and the first people in the crowd began to see her, their voices grew."

    old "Rising from a murmur to a loud war chant."
    new "Rising from a murmur to a loud war chant."

    old "Stomping their plated boots to the rhythm of their own chants, battering the street stone with their spears."
    new "Stomping their plated boots to the rhythm of their own chants, battering the street stone with their spears."

    old "Smashing their armored gloves against their heavy shields."
    new "Smashing their armored gloves against their heavy shields."

    old "All of the city felt as if it echoed their bloodlust."
    new "All of the city felt as if it echoed their bloodlust."

    old "Throwing up her arms, the army erupted into an ever louder scream."
    new "Throwing up her arms, the army erupted into an ever louder scream."

    old "Sarah was too far above to speak to them, but they understood her well enough by her body alone."
    new "Sarah was too far above to speak to them, but they understood her well enough by her body alone."

    old "Besides, she thought, she was not even really human to most of them."
    new "Besides, she thought, she was not even really human to most of them."

    old "Most of them she had never met and likely never would."
    new "Most of them she had never met and likely never would."

    old "To them...she was symbol."
    new "To them...she was symbol."

    old "A divine omen, one that made victory so obvious that it made them eager for the bloodshed."
    new "A divine omen, one that made victory so obvious that it made them eager for the bloodshed."

    old "And looking down, feeling the pounding of their blades and chants, Sarah saw an army unlike any other."
    new "And looking down, feeling the pounding of their blades and chants, Sarah saw an army unlike any other."

    old "One that would not be defeated. Would not be broken."
    new "One that would not be defeated. Would not be broken."

    old "Perhaps the world had known larger armies. Perhaps it had known better armed and trained armies."
    new "Perhaps the world had known larger armies. Perhaps it had known better armed and trained armies."

    old "But had it ever known one more motivated than this one?"
    new "But had it ever known one more motivated than this one?"

    old "They continued their screams as she looked out over them."
    new "They continued their screams as she looked out over them."

    old "On the far end, Sarah could see the citizens of Rahayal."
    new "On the far end, Sarah could see the citizens of Rahayal."

    old "They looked on with dispassionate interest. They cared little for the Union Kingdoms, but they cared for a spectacle."
    new "They looked on with dispassionate interest. They cared little for the Union Kingdoms, but they cared for a spectacle."

    old "But in the cauldron below, the emotions of her people climbed ever higher."
    new "But in the cauldron below, the emotions of her people climbed ever higher."

    old "Battering all the walls of the city, shaking the rock upon which Rahayal was build."
    new "Battering all the walls of the city, shaking the rock upon which Rahayal was build."

    old "Sarah smiled, content in knowing that she had the army she needed."
    new "Sarah smiled, content in knowing that she had the army she needed."

    old "She turned and left, fearing that any more might inspire a riot."
    new "She turned and left, fearing that any more might inspire a riot."

    old "As she stepped back into the room, Sarah could hear the crowd still chanting."
    new "As she stepped back into the room, Sarah could hear the crowd still chanting."

    old "Inside, sheltered from the sharp sun, it felt cooler."
    new "Inside, sheltered from the sharp sun, it felt cooler."

    old "The adrenaline of seeing her army, her people, slowly subsiding."
    new "The adrenaline of seeing her army, her people, slowly subsiding."

    old "She sat down at her chair, exhausted."
    new "She sat down at her chair, exhausted."

    old "Everything had been planned. Everything discussed and debated, a dozen times over."
    new "Everything had been planned. Everything discussed and debated, a dozen times over."

    old "Oaths sworn, words spoken."
    new "Oaths sworn, words spoken."

    old "Now, all those preparations would become fact."
    new "Now, all those preparations would become fact."

    old "Her soldiers would be slowly boarding the ships by now."
    new "Her soldiers would be slowly boarding the ships by now."

    old "In a few hours, they would be ready to depart."
    new "In a few hours, they would be ready to depart."

    old "And Sarah looked about the room. Quiet."
    new "And Sarah looked about the room. Quiet."

    old "She had spend so much time doubting herself, questioning if this was the right thing to do."
    new "She had spend so much time doubting herself, questioning if this was the right thing to do."

    old "Now, all doubt was gone from her heart."
    new "Now, all doubt was gone from her heart."

    old "And only the worry remained."
    new "And only the worry remained."

    old "Yet it was not the fear of her own position that she worried for."
    new "Yet it was not the fear of her own position that she worried for."

    old "Instead, only the lives that would be lost."
    new "Instead, only the lives that would be lost."

    old "No war was won without deaths."
    new "No war was won without deaths."

    old "This one would be no different."
    new "This one would be no different."

    old "Some of the men below whose hearts now beat fast with eager bloodlust would soon be stilled by a Tribesman's blade."
    new "Some of the men below whose hearts now beat fast with eager bloodlust would soon be stilled by a Tribesman's blade."

    old "Even in victory, some suffered."
    new "Even in victory, some suffered."

    old "Would they think it worth it as they died, she wondered?"
    new "Would they think it worth it as they died, she wondered?"

    old "Knowing that they died for a cause they believed in?"
    new "Knowing that they died for a cause they believed in?"

    old "Perhaps that was a better death than most could hope for in this world, she thought."
    new "Perhaps that was a better death than most could hope for in this world, she thought."

    old "Closing her eyes, Sarah took in the few quiet moments that the world still afforded her."
    new "Closing her eyes, Sarah took in the few quiet moments that the world still afforded her."

    old "A knock at the door startled her."
    new "A knock at the door startled her."

    old "She looked about, disoriented."
    new "She looked about, disoriented."

    old "Had she dozed off?"
    new "Had she dozed off?"

    old "Yes, come in!"
    new "Yes, come in!"

    old "Lady Carolyn entered the room."
    new "Lady Carolyn entered the room."

    old "Sleeping, were we?"
    new "Sleeping, were we?"

    old "Sarah felt awkard at how easily Carolyn always seemed to read her."
    new "Sarah felt awkard at how easily Carolyn always seemed to read her."

    old "Yeah...I might have been more tired than I thought."
    new "Yeah...I might have been more tired than I thought."

    old "Well, it's fine that you managed to get some rest."
    new "Well, it's fine that you managed to get some rest."

    old "Boarding of the ships has been progressing quite well."
    new "Boarding of the ships has been progressing quite well."

    old "They'll soon be ready for you to step onto the flagship."
    new "They'll soon be ready for you to step onto the flagship."

    old "Flagship. They called it that, and thought it was an impressive ship among the armada, it wasn't much compared to most warships."
    new "Flagship. They called it that, and thought it was an impressive ship among the armada, it wasn't much compared to most warships."

    old "The Tribesmen famously did not have any navy, and the old Rosannan fleet had fled after the fall."
    new "The Tribesmen famously did not have any navy, and the old Rosannan fleet had fled after the fall."

    old "The ships they had hired were not warships. Their only real goal was to transport her army across the ocean, back to Rosanna."
    new "The ships they had hired were not warships. Their only real goal was to transport her army across the ocean, back to Rosanna."

    old "Still, they couldn't allow themselves to be entirely vulnerable to pirates."
    new "Still, they couldn't allow themselves to be entirely vulnerable to pirates."

    old "Good. I think I have most of what I need."
    new "Good. I think I have most of what I need."

    old "Carolyn laughed as she saw Sarah's bag."
    new "Carolyn laughed as she saw Sarah's bag."

    old "Nothing...just that I remember the girl you used to be."
    new "Nothing...just that I remember the girl you used to be."

    old "What's that supposed to mean?"
    new "What's that supposed to mean?"

    old "That girl used to have more stuff propped into one dresser than what you carry around in that bag."
    new "That girl used to have more stuff propped into one dresser than what you carry around in that bag."

    old "Mercenary life learns you to pack light, among other things."
    new "Mercenary life learns you to pack light, among other things."

    old "So much the same. So much changed."
    new "So much the same. So much changed."

    old "A quiet pause lingered for a moment."
    new "A quiet pause lingered for a moment."

    old "Well, come then. We will take my coach to the harbor and I'll join you up to the flagship."
    new "Well, come then. We will take my coach to the harbor and I'll join you up to the flagship."

    old "Carolyn was smart, Sarah thought to herself."
    new "Carolyn was smart, Sarah thought to herself."

    old "Already she was making sure that anywhere Sarah went, Carolyn would be seen by her side."
    new "Already she was making sure that anywhere Sarah went, Carolyn would be seen by her side."

    old "Making sure that when this was all over, everyone understood how integral she had been to the whole campaign."
    new "Making sure that when this was all over, everyone understood how integral she had been to the whole campaign."

    old "Securing her seat in the new court before it had even properly been formed."
    new "Securing her seat in the new court before it had even properly been formed."

    old "Sure, let's go."
    new "Sure, let's go."

    old "Sarah picked up her singular bag and joined Lady Carolyn."
    new "Sarah picked up her singular bag and joined Lady Carolyn."

    old "Together, they walked through the Estate, outside and stepped into the coach that was waiting for them."
    new "Together, they walked through the Estate, outside and stepped into the coach that was waiting for them."

    old "Neither spoke much. A weight seemed to linger over both of them."
    new "Neither spoke much. A weight seemed to linger over both of them."

    old "It wasn't a day for idle chatter."
    new "It wasn't a day for idle chatter."

    old "In silence, they rode together to the harbor."
    new "In silence, they rode together to the harbor."

    old "Sarah looked about as she took in the city of Rahayal for the last time."
    new "Sarah looked about as she took in the city of Rahayal for the last time."

    old "A few people in the street seemed to notice them go by, but most went about their day."
    new "A few people in the street seemed to notice them go by, but most went about their day."

    old "Same as any other for most of them."
    new "Same as any other for most of them."

    old "A family working at an inn looked up as they passed, sparing them a glance."
    new "A family working at an inn looked up as they passed, sparing them a glance."

    old "Then they were gone."
    new "Then they were gone."

    old "Whole lives, Sarah thought to herself, entirely seperate from her own."
    new "Whole lives, Sarah thought to herself, entirely seperate from her own."

    old "Spared from the carnage she'd soon unleash."
    new "Spared from the carnage she'd soon unleash."

    old "Sarah tried to appreciate the marvels of the city, but her mind kept wandering back to her army."
    new "Sarah tried to appreciate the marvels of the city, but her mind kept wandering back to her army."

    old "The greatest city in the world, and today, it might as well have been nothing at all to her."
    new "The greatest city in the world, and today, it might as well have been nothing at all to her."

    old "Their coach pulled up to the harbor and Sarah and Carolyn got out."
    new "Their coach pulled up to the harbor and Sarah and Carolyn got out."

    old "As Sarah got out of the coach, she saw the thousands of people turning their heads to catch a glimpse of her."
    new "As Sarah got out of the coach, she saw the thousands of people turning their heads to catch a glimpse of her."

    old "Back in the city, to the people of Rahayal, she didn't mean much."
    new "Back in the city, to the people of Rahayal, she didn't mean much."

    old "Here, she saw the worship on their faces."
    new "Here, she saw the worship on their faces."

    old "To them, she was everything."
    new "To them, she was everything."

    old "Sarah slowly scanned the army. Preparations were still in full swing, countless people moving about like a colony of ants."
    new "Sarah slowly scanned the army. Preparations were still in full swing, countless people moving about like a colony of ants."

    old "Out in the harbor, more ships than she had ever seen at one moment in her life."
    new "Out in the harbor, more ships than she had ever seen at one moment in her life."

    old "As she began to walk across the dock towards the flagship, she saw the men and women of Rosanna."
    new "As she began to walk across the dock towards the flagship, she saw the men and women of Rosanna."

    old "Some greeted her, others seemed stunned at seeing her so close; more cheering her name."
    new "Some greeted her, others seemed stunned at seeing her so close; more cheering her name."

    old "Princess. Commander. Rose Knight. Mage Killer. Demon Slayer."
    new "Princess. Commander. Rose Knight. Mage Killer. Demon Slayer."

    old "More titles than she knew what to do with, and they cried them all out."
    new "More titles than she knew what to do with, and they cried them all out."

    old "Some of the men she had served with for years in the mercenary company. Others her own people, sons and daughters of Rosanna, eager to return home."
    new "Some of the men she had served with for years in the mercenary company. Others her own people, sons and daughters of Rosanna, eager to return home."

    old "Sarah smiled and waved at all of them."
    new "Sarah smiled and waved at all of them."

    old "Still, she felt a distance between herself and others that she had not felt in years."
    new "Still, she felt a distance between herself and others that she had not felt in years."

    old "Sarah lowed her head and walked up the gangway."
    new "Sarah lowed her head and walked up the gangway."

    old "Stepping onto the deck of the ship, she heard the wood creak."
    new "Stepping onto the deck of the ship, she heard the wood creak."

    old "Around her, sailors and soldiers were rushing to prepare for departure."
    new "Around her, sailors and soldiers were rushing to prepare for departure."

    old "The sky above seemed clear. The wind and sea, calm."
    new "The sky above seemed clear. The wind and sea, calm."

    old "Good fortunes, she thought to herself. She hoped it would stay this way."
    new "Good fortunes, she thought to herself. She hoped it would stay this way."

    old "Below, she could look out across most of the harbor."
    new "Below, she could look out across most of the harbor."

    old "The preparations that were being carried out on the flagship, were being carried out a hundred times over, all across the harbor."
    new "The preparations that were being carried out on the flagship, were being carried out a hundred times over, all across the harbor."

    old "Each ship would carry hundreds of soldiers across the sea."
    new "Each ship would carry hundreds of soldiers across the sea."

    old "Back home."
    new "Back home."

    old "Memories of fleeing her home came back to her."
    new "Memories of fleeing her home came back to her."

    old "When she had first left, she had never imagined it would be this long before she would return."
    new "When she had first left, she had never imagined it would be this long before she would return."

    old "Yet still, she also struggled to imagine the girl she had been all that time ago."
    new "Yet still, she also struggled to imagine the girl she had been all that time ago."

    old "Memories of someone softer, that now seemed so strange to her."
    new "Memories of someone softer, that now seemed so strange to her."

    old "As if everything before had happened to someone else."
    new "As if everything before had happened to someone else."

    old "Only Thomas still haunted her, no less than the day she heard of his defeat."
    new "Only Thomas still haunted her, no less than the day she heard of his defeat."

    old "Above her, she saw the sail of the ship, twist in the wind."
    new "Above her, she saw the sail of the ship, twist in the wind."

    old "She said his name, softly to herself."
    new "She said his name, softly to herself."

    old "He should have been here with her, she thought. Together, reclaiming their home."
    new "He should have been here with her, she thought. Together, reclaiming their home."

    old "Or she should have been with him, defending it to the very end."
    new "Or she should have been with him, defending it to the very end."

    old "No matter how she reasoned it, something about her life felt deeply wrong."
    new "No matter how she reasoned it, something about her life felt deeply wrong."

    old "But she would make it right, she vowed to herself."
    new "But she would make it right, she vowed to herself."

    old "With her ships and her army, she would turn the world back to how it should have been."
    new "With her ships and her army, she would turn the world back to how it should have been."

    old "Repair it, if only a little."
    new "Repair it, if only a little."

    old "Sarah continued to stand at the edge of the ship, looking out."
    new "Sarah continued to stand at the edge of the ship, looking out."

    old "She heard Lady Carolyn approach."
    new "She heard Lady Carolyn approach."

    old "The first formation will be ready soon."
    new "The first formation will be ready soon."

    old "The others will follow after."
    new "The others will follow after."

    old "It will be enough."
    new "It will be enough."

    old "She wasn't sure if she said it because she believed it, or because she was trying to comfort herself."
    new "She wasn't sure if she said it because she believed it, or because she was trying to comfort herself."

    old "As soon as you give the signal, we'll set sail."
    new "As soon as you give the signal, we'll set sail."

    old "Closing her eyes, she took in the city with all her other senses."
    new "Closing her eyes, she took in the city with all her other senses."

    old "The noise of the army. The salt smell of the sea. The wind on her face."
    new "The noise of the army. The salt smell of the sea. The wind on her face."

    old "One by one, each drowned out, until only a quiet focus remained."
    new "One by one, each drowned out, until only a quiet focus remained."

    old "When Sarah opened her eyes again, she saw the world, sharpened."
    new "When Sarah opened her eyes again, she saw the world, sharpened."

    old "Give the order."
    new "Give the order."

    old "We set sail."
    new "We set sail."

